@startuml
title Host coordination — handoff on `currentStep.host` change

skinparam shadowing false

actor User
participant "OnboardingActivity\n(host observer)" as OA
participant "LinearOnboarding-\nOrchestrator" as Orch
participant "BrowserActivity\n(host observer)" as BA

== OnboardingActivity foreground (currentStep.host = OnboardingActivity) ==

User -> OA : taps primary on last\nOnboardingActivity-hosted step
OA -> Orch : onEvent(...)
Orch -> Orch : advance →\ncurrentStep changes\nhost = BrowserActivity
Orch --> OA : state emits\nInProgress(..., currentStep.host = BrowserActivity)
OA -> OA : host mismatch
OA -> BA : startActivity(intent)
OA -> OA : finish()

== BrowserActivity foreground ==

BA -> Orch : observe orchestrator.state
Orch --> BA : InProgress(..., currentStep.host = BrowserActivity)
BA -> BA : host matches → render

note over OA, BA
  Both activities run the same observer logic symmetrically.
  When the user finishes a BrowserActivity-hosted step and the
  next step's host is OnboardingActivity, the roles flip:
  BrowserActivity launches OnboardingActivity and finish()es.
end note

@enduml
